        <item>
            <title>0.7.0</title>
            <pubDate>Tue, 21 Jul 2026 13:48:35 +0200</pubDate>
            <sparkle:version>700</sparkle:version>
            <sparkle:shortVersionString>0.7.0</sparkle:shortVersionString>
            <sparkle:minimumSystemVersion>14.0</sparkle:minimumSystemVersion>
            <sparkle:hardwareRequirements>arm64</sparkle:hardwareRequirements>
            <description><![CDATA[<h2>Jarvis 0.7.0</h2>
<p><b>Your day, complete.</b> The task loop closes: Jarvis now shows the tasks it
finds in your world — and notices when you've finished them.</p>
<ul>
  <li><b>"Your day"</b> — a new home for your tasks: things people asked of you,
      things you promised, and suggestions Jarvis noticed, each backed by the
      verbatim message it came from. A live badge shows what needs you.</li>
  <li><b>Task details</b> — open any task to see the source conversation, jump to
      it in Slack/Gmail/Meetings, mark done, snooze, or dismiss.</li>
  <li><b>"Looks done?"</b> — when you post that you've finished something
      ("shipped it", "sent it over"), Jarvis suggests marking the task done —
      with the exact message as evidence. You confirm with one click; Jarvis
      never closes a task by itself.</li>
  <li><b>For agents</b> — a new <code>list_tasks</code> MCP tool so Claude Code
      and other agents can see your open tasks.</li>
</ul>
]]></description>
